        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 3:50PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>Atmospheric conditions are favorable for the development of funnel
clouds. These funnel clouds normally only protrude a few hundred
feet downward from the parent cloud, rotate or spin like a top,
and last a few minutes before dissipating.

If storms continue to intensify, conditions this afternoon may
support a threat for brief landspout tornadoes or even a few low-
topped or mini supercell tornadoes.

If threatening weather approaches, move indoors to a place of
safety. The National Weather Service will continue to closely
monitor the situation, and will issue warnings, if necessary.
</description>
